                <note rend="inline" type="source">300.115(39) City of Flint/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_SLA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-24T17:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 24, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 24—12:36 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>793. My 789, October 24, 10 [<hi rend="italic">9</hi>] a.m. I saw <persName
                        corresp="#p_PVP1">Potemkin</persName> at 3 o’clock this afternoon. He stated
                    that he had no other information than appeared in the Tass despatch quoted in my
                    telegram under reference but that in anticipation of my call he had requested
                    the Soviet naval authorities at Murmansk to let him have a full report as
                    quickly as possible and that he would advise me as soon as all of the facts were
                    in his possession.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
